dct_description_sm: California with nearly flat northern coast and many coastal place names. TERRA ESONIS INCOGNITA and Fretum Anian to northwest, and Paye de Moozemleck to north.
Title cartouche (lower left) with one seated native near an elephant and lion.
Column of text to map right explains map abbreviations.
Similar to map of same title issued by Schrieber, 1749, except for changed cartouche (Entry 233).
Issued in his: Atlas minor ex tabulis geographicis. -- [Augsburg, 1784?].
verlegt von loh: Mich: Probst in Augsburg.
